ðŸ” Definition

A SQL JOIN is used to combine rows from two or more tables based on a common column between them.
It retrieves data that is related logically between multiple tables.

ðŸ§© Basic Syntax
SELECT columns_from_both_tables
FROM table1
JOIN table2
ON table1.column1 = table2.column2;


Explanation:

table1 and table2 â†’ Tables you want to join

column1 and column2 â†’ Common columns between the two tables

The ON keyword specifies the matching condition

Example 1 â€” Join Two Tables Based on a Common Column

